<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-268-049 </DOCNO><DOCID>08 445 034</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Seybold Report on Publishing Systems  April 30 1990 v19 n16p27(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Seybold Publications Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>L300 calibration software. (LinoCal Mac-based calibrationsoftware) (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Linotype Co. (product introduction).andO;Product:   LinoCal (Performance analysis software) (product introduction)Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (computer programs).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionCalibrationSoftware Packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>L300 calibration software The Mac-based calibration software that Linotypeshowed will certainly be a boon to all those who are running an L300 withoutcalibration, or to those who aren't sure if they are going about thisimportant task in quite the right way.andP;  Linotype is calling the productLinoCal and is introducing it to users with a $195 half-day seminar to beheld at locations across the country.andM;Training and Support.andP;  A key component in any such product, of course, ismaking sure the customer knows how to use it.andP;  Linotype has already beenemphasizing that it adds value by selecting packages that work well togetherfor its Series 1000 software line.andP;  It has now formally begun sellingtraining to its users.andM;Linotype will offer a series of classes for the hardware and software it haschosen for its publishing systems.andP;  In addition to the one on using the newcalibration software, another will be held in early May that focuses onscanning and working with halftones.andM;The company will also offer a remote diagnostic function called Lino-Care.andO;Using a popular communications program (Farallon's Timbuktu), the Linotypetechnician can literally call up and take control of the user's workstation,allowing the technician to &quot;see&quot; what is going on and try various solutions.andO;It won't help if your Mac itself is the problem, however.andM;IBM and other computer companies (as well as Atex and other major newspapersystem vendors) have long used remote diagnostics for scoping out mainframeproblems, but this is new for imagesetter companies.andO;</TEXT></DOC>